# Claude (opus) — 2026-03-17 11:56:47
# Duration: 743s — Exit: 0
# Prompt:
#   /spec:create Improve title extraction algorithm based on feedback from iteration 28
#   
#   Context for spec creation:
#   - Read the feedback at tools/title-loop/docs/28-1ac016c/feedback.md
#   - Read the current implementation at lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts
#   - Read previous iteration docs in tools/title-loop/docs/ to understand what has been tried
#   
#   Hard constraints:
#   - Must run on a mobile device (React Native / Expo)
#   - Total title extraction must complete under 10 seconds
#   - Changes land in lib/text-classifier/ and related files
#   
#   Everything else is open for debate. The current approach (MiniLM embeddings + heuristic scoring)
#   is one option, but you are free to propose alternatives if they'd work better:
#   - Different embedding model or similarity strategy
#   - Replacing embeddings entirely with a rule-based or hybrid approach
#   - Restructuring the pipeline (e.g., two-pass, re-ranking, candidate merging)
#   - Changing how candidates are generated, filtered, or deduplicated
#   - Any other approach that solves the failures within the hard constraints
#   
#   Don't be incremental for the sake of it — if the feedback reveals a fundamental design flaw,
#   propose a fundamental fix. But also don't change things that already work well.
#   
#   IMPORTANT: Write the spec to tools/title-loop/docs/28-1ac016c/improvement-plan.md (not to specs/ directory).
#   Do NOT modify any code files. Only write the improvement-plan.md file.

============================================================

The improvement plan is written to `tools/title-loop/docs/28-1ac016c/improvement-plan.md`.

**Key findings:** The iteration 27 plan identified the right patterns but had implementation bugs. By reading the actual test files and tracing through the code, I found 5 specific root causes:

1. **`1→l` instead of `1→i`** (6 cases) — The blind OCR repair always maps digit `1` to letter `l` in mixed case, but recipe words need `i` (`Bra1sed` → `Braised`). Fix: generate both `i` and `l` variants and let the embedding scorer pick the winner.

2. **English food categories missing from hard filters** (3 cases) — Polish categories like "warzywa" are in `SECTION_LABELS` but English equivalents like "vegetables" aren't. `VEGETABLES` and `FISH & SEAFOOD` become candidates instead of being filtered. Fix: add `isCategorySectionLabel` to hard filters.

3. **Blank line between header and title** (2 cases) — The direct-successor bonus checks `lines[position-1]` which is blank. Fix: scan backward to the nearest non-empty line.

4. **Overflow marker regex too narrow** (1 case) — `[CORRUPTED TEXT FROM PREVIOUS PAGE]` doesn't match. Fix: broaden regex.

5. **Non-consecutive instruction prologues** (1 case) — Spillover mixes instructions and prose, breaking consecutive-line detection. Fix: count both types together.
