{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HpdMmDzLPuN167FK9FTWKT","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create a final summary document based on all the information gathered.\n\n## Summary: Title Extraction System for Recipe Photo App\n\nI've thoroughly reviewed the title extraction system for Fasola, the recipe photo management app. Here's what I found:\n\n### Current State (Iteration 28)\n\n**Performance:**\n- 90.1% overall accuracy (combined score on generated files)\n- 100% accuracy on real files (11/11)\n- All 11 failures are on generated/synthetic test files, not real user photos\n\n**Iteration progression (from iter.txt):**\n- Iterations 1-17: Rapid improvements from 16.7% → 90.9%\n- Iterations 18-26: Plateau phase with 72-85% accuracy\n- Iterations 25-28: Stabilized at 90-100% on real files\n  - Iteration 25: 100% on real files (1 real failure in compound title handling)\n  - Iteration 26-27: 100% on real files, plateau on generated\n  - Iteration 28: 100% on real files, same plateau\n\n### Key Failure Patterns (11 cases in Iteration 28, all generated)\n\n**Pattern 1: OCR digit-for-letter corruption (5 failures)**\n- Examples: `Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne`, `D1p`, `Sern1k`\n- Behavior: Extractor returns empty or falls back to random body lines\n- Root cause: Dictionary-based OCR repair misses out-of-vocabulary words; embedding score penalizes corrupted text\n\n**Pattern 2: Category header precedes title (3 failures)**\n- Examples: `FISH & SEAFOOD` then title 2 lines later, pipe-delimited metadata `Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB` before title\n- Behavior: Extracts section header, subtitle, or empty\n- Root cause: First-after-preamble bonus insufficient; pipe-delimited metadata not fully handled\n\n**Pattern 3: Multi-line split titles (previously 1 failure, now fixed)**\n- Example: `LEMON HERB RO45TED` + `VEGETABLES` should become `LEMON HERB ROASTED VEGETABLES`\n- Current status: Iteration 28 shows partial success - extracts `LEMON HERB ROASTED + LEMON HERB ROASTED VEGETABLES`\n\n**Pattern 4: Title absent from page start (2 failures)**\n- Examples: `Mushroom Risotto`, `Peach Cobbler` - files start with previous recipe's content\n- Behavior: Extracts different recipe's title or instruction lines\n- Root cause: Spillover detection not catching implicit patterns; multi-recipe corroboration weak\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\nThe extraction pipeline (`lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`, 1577 lines) has these stages:\n\n1. **Preprocessing**: Skip garbled burst (short OCR noise at start)\n2. **Pre-merge**: Join continuation lines (e.g., `PIZZA / VARIATION`)\n3. **Candidate generation**: Single lines + 2-line and 3-line joins\n4. **Hard filters**: 9 independent checks (length, ingredients, metadata, OCR quality, sections, etc.)\n5. **Pre-filter cap**: Limit to 25 candidates, preferring ALL_CAPS and short ones\n6. **Embedding scoring**: Semantic similarity to \"recipe name, dish title...\" minus header/noise similarity\n7. **Bonuses**: Position (multiplicative x1.0-1.12), ALL_CAPS (+0.08), structural (+0.10)\n8. **Bilingual detection**: Suppress ALL_CAPS translations that conflict with mixed-case titles\n9. **Threshold filtering**: max(0.08, bestThresholdScore × 0.7)\n10. **Post-threshold cleanup**: Remove prefixes, join protection, sub-section removal\n11. **Dedup**: Shorter substring wins\n12. **Multi-title guard**: Check ingredient gaps, corroboration\n13. **Final sort & join**: Return up to 3 titles joined with \" + \"\n\n### Recent Implementation Improvements\n\n**Iteration 27→28 changes (planned but status unclear):**\n- Iteration 27 added \"direct-successor bonus\" for lines immediately following section headers\n- Working toward fixing OCR blind repair for early-position candidates\n- Planned: Extend corroboration to check post-spillover text only\n\n**Language support:**\n- English: 80+ measurement units, metadata patterns (SERVES, PREP TIME, etc.)\n- Polish: 40+ units (łyżka, szklanka, szczypta), metadata (NA, DLA, MIN, GODZ), section labels (SKŁADNIKI, PRZYGOTOWANIE)\n\n### Failure Analysis Detail\n\n**Iteration 26 feedback** (16 generated failures, 0 real):\n- Spillover corruption: 5 failures (empty extraction when page starts with previous recipe)\n- Heavy digit corruption: 2 failures (titles with dense digit substitution rejected)\n- Wrong body text: 3 failures (partial corruption causes fallback to instructions/serving text)\n- Section headers: 3 failures (category headers like FISH & SEAFOOD scored too high)\n- Multi-line title truncation: 1 failure (only first line extracted)\n- Mid-recipe pages: 2 failures (multiple recipes on same page)\n\n**Iteration 27 feedback** (11 generated, 0 real):\n- Same core patterns as iteration 26, suggesting the improvements didn't fully resolve root causes\n\n### File Locations\n\n- Implementation: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n- Iteration tracking: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/iter.txt`\n- Recent feedback:\n  - Iteration 28: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/28-1ac016c/feedback.md` (5.3KB)\n  - Iteration 27: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/27-51f970e/feedback.md` (4.3KB)\n  - Iteration 27 plan: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/27-51f970e/improvement-plan.md` (18KB, very detailed)\n- Architecture docs: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/architecture.md`\n\n### Key Insights\n\n1. **Real vs synthetic gap**: 100% success on real files but plateau on generated tests suggests the synthetic test generation may not fully replicate real OCR patterns\n2. **Diminishing returns on dictionary approach**: Iteration 24-26 expanded food dictionary but OCR failures persist - blind repair may be needed\n3. **Position bonus limitations**: Current multiplicative position bonus (x1.0-1.12) insufficient to overcome semantic similarity scores of descriptive text\n4. **Spillover detection gap**: Can detect explicit markers but implicit spillover (pages starting mid-instruction) not fully caught\n5. **Compound architecture stability**: The pipeline has ~1500 lines of carefully balanced heuristics; each fix risks subtle regressions elsewhere\n\nThe improvement plan for iteration 28 is thorough and well-documented, with 4 targeted fixes, implementation order, and testing strategy already mapped out."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af6c96954152952e6 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 114885\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 74848</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"9f320b1e-6125-4111-87be-35479fda61d9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the title extraction system for a recipe photo app. Please gather:\n\n1. Read tools/title-loop/docs/28-1ac016c/feedback.md - this is the iteration 28 feedback\n2. Read tools/title-loop/docs/28-1ac016c/ - list all files in this directory\n3. Read the current implementation at lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts\n4. List all directories in tools/title-loop/docs/ to see iteration history\n5. Read the most recent iteration docs (iteration 25-27) to understand recent changes - look for feedback.md or similar files in each\n6. Read tools/title-loop/docs/iter.txt for iteration tracking info\n\nBe thorough - read every file completely. I need the full content of feedback.md especially.","agentId":"af6c96954152952e6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create a final summary document based on all the information gathered.\n\n## Summary: Title Extraction System for Recipe Photo App\n\nI've thoroughly reviewed the title extraction system for Fasola, the recipe photo management app. Here's what I found:\n\n### Current State (