{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RGRg5U32Wovyt6PfNrP7CP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne\n     2→\n     3→(OCR CORRUPTION: digit for letter, hyphenation)\n     4→\n     5→lngredients:\n     6→\n     7→800g cod fillets (or so1e)\n     8→300m1 wh1te w1ne (dry)\n     9→2 onions, sliced\n    10→4 cloves garl-ic, m1nced\n    11→200g mushshrooms, sliced\n    12→100m1 f1sh broth\n    13→3 tbsp ol1ve oil\n    14→2 tbsp but-ter\n    15→1 tbsp d1ll (fresh or dried)\n    16→lemon, juiced\n    17→sa1t and pepper to taste\n    18→bay leaf\n    19→\n    20→lnstructions:\n    21→\n    22→1. Heat ol1ve oil 1n a large pan. Brown cod filets on both s1des, 3-4 m1nutes each.\n    23→2. Remove cod and set as1de.\n    24→3. 1n the same pan, sauté onions and garl1c for 5 m1nutes.\n    25→4. Add mushrooms, cook 4-5 more m1nutes.\n    26→5. Deglaze pan w1th wh1te w1ne, scraping up brown b1ts.\n    27→6. Add fish broth, bay leaf, and lemon ju1ce.\n    28→7. Return cod to pan, reduce heat to medium-low.\n    29→8. S1mmer for 12-15 m1nutes unt1l cod flakes eas1ly.\n    30→9. St1r in butter and fresh d1ll.\n    31→10. Season w1th salt and pepper.\n    32→\n    33→Serve w1th roasted potatoes and crusty bread.\n    34→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkGVRfuYHRcmb4gr5mY2s8","session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"681501f5-438a-4397-bf6c-e16de153ce02"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q7BKUBpF8yhVT8pCxb4JKu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FISH & SEAFOOD\n     2→\n     3→Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\n     4→\n     5→An elegant fish dish with a subtle floral note from\n     6→saffron. Perfect for entertaining.\n     7→\n     8→Ingredients:\n     9→- 4 halibut fillets (150g each)\n    10→- 1 teaspoon saffron threads\n    11→- 1/4 cup hot water\n    12→- 200ml heavy cream\n    13→- 2 shallots, finely diced\n    14→- 100ml dry white wine\n    15→- 2 tablespoons butter\n    16→- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n    17→- Salt and white pepper\n    18→- Fresh dill for garnish\n    19→- 1 lemon, for serving\n    20→\n    21→Instructions:\n    22→Steep saffron threads in hot water for 10 minutes. 67\n    23→Heat butter and olive oil in pan over medium-high heat.\n    24→Season halibut with salt and pepper.\n    25→Cook fillets 4-5 minutes per side until cooked through.\n    26→Remove and keep warm.\n    27→In same pan, sauté shallots until softened.\n    28→Add white wine, reduce by half.\n    29→Pour in saffron water and cream.\n    30→Simmer 3-4 minutes until slightly thickened.\n    31→Return halibut to pan, coat with sauce.\n    32→Serve garnished with fresh dill and lemon wedge.\n    33→Serves 4."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkGVRfuYHRcmb4gr5mY2s8","session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"f94c1b76-ad2c-4e85-88d1-7efa4e7a2c52"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MywQiY9QNgVYu9kTeroSyj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Reduce heat and stir in the remaining stock, one ladle at a time, until the rice is\n     2→creamy but still al dente, about 18-20 minutes. The risotto should flow slightly on the plate.\n     3→Season with salt and white pepper. Finish with butter and grated Parmigiano-Reggiano.\n     4→\n     5→CARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\n     6→\n     7→Slice the swordfish paper-thin. Arrange on chilled plates. Dress with extra virgin olive oil,\n     8→lemon juice, and sea salt. Scatter thinly shaved fennel and microgreens. Serve immediately.\n     9→\n    10→Preparation: 10 minutes\n    11→Serves: 4\n    12→\n    13→CARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\n    14→\n    15→Place thin slices on a cold plate. Whisk together lemon, lime, orange juice with good quality\n    16→oil. Season with fıne sea salt and crushed coriander seeds. Garnish with fresh herbs and\n    17→thinly sliced radish.\n    18→\n    19→nto a loured work counter and knead until smooth, approx 8 minutes. Proof in oiled bowl, cover\n    20→with damp cloth, 45 minutes at room temperature. Shape into ½ dozen rounds. Second proof 30 min.\n    21→\n    22→Place pans in 225°C/435-VI0.. oven for 12-15 minutes until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.\n    23→\n    24→Makes: 1 dozen\n    25→\n    26→FRESH PASTA DOUGH\n    27→\n    28→125 grams plain flour\n    29→½ cup plus ı tablespoon water\n    30→Pinch of sea salt\n    31→\n    32→Combine flour and slt on work bench. Make well in center. Add water gradually, mixing with fork\n    33→until dough comes together. Knead 5 minutes.\n    34→\n    35→Mushroom Risotto\n    36→\n    37→Ingredients:\n    38→300g arborio rice\n    39→1 liter vegetable stock\n    40→250g mixed mushrooms, sliced\n    41→1 medium onion, finely diced\n    42→100ml dry white wine\n    43→50g butter\n    44→50g parmesan cheese, grated\n    45→2 tablespoons olive oil\n    46→Salt and white pepper to taste\n    47→Fresh parsley for garnish\n    48→\n    49→Method:\n    50→Heat stock in separate pan and keep at gentle simmer. Heat olive oil in large risotto pan over\n    51→medium heat. Sauté onion until translucent, about 3 minutes. Add mushrooms and cook until\n    52→golden, approximately 5 minutes. Add rice and stir constantly for 2 minutes to toast grains.\n    53→\n    54→Deglaze with white wine and stir until absorbed. Begin adding warm stock one ladle at a time,\n    55→stirring frequently. Each addition should be absorbed before adding more stock, taking about\n    56→18-20 minutes total. The rice should be creamy yet retain a slight firmness to the bite.\n    57→\n    58→Finish risotto by stirring in butter and grated parmesan cheese. Season with salt and white\n    59→pepper to taste. Transfer to serving bowl and garnish with fresh parsley and additional cheese.\n    60→\n    61→Serves: 4-6\n    62→Preparation time: 10 minutes\n    63→Cooking time: 30 minutes\n    64→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkGVRfuYHRcmb4gr5mY2s8","session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"7b32ba3f-6b23-4bd4-a693-8fbdc05748cf"}
