{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LVKdF5hCuiTJoUwzrixfYq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | PRZYGOTOWANIE 15 MIN | GOTOWANIE 20 MIN\n     2→\n     3→OGÓRKOWA ZUPA\n     4→\n     5→Ogórkowa zupa, or Polish cucumber soup, is a refreshing summer soup served\n     6→either hot or cold. The dill-infused broth is bright and tangy, perfect for\n     7→warm days when you want something light yet satisfying and nourishing.\n     8→\n     9→INGREDIENTS:\n    10→- 6 medium cucumbers, peeled and diced\n    11→- 6 cups vegetable or chicken stock\n    12→- 1 large onion, diced\n    13→- 2 tbsp butter\n    14→- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n    15→- 3 tbsp fresh dill, chopped\n    16→- 2 tbsp fresh lemon juice\n    17→- 1/2 cup sour cream\n    18→- 1/4 tsp white pepper\n    19→- Salt to taste\n    20→- Fresh dill sprigs for garnish\n    21→\n    22→INSTRUCTIONS:\n    23→1. In a large pot, melt butter over medium heat.\n    24→2. Sauté diced onion until translucent, about 5 minutes.\n    25→3. Add minced garlic and cook 1 minute more.\n    26→4. Add diced cucumbers and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n    27→5. Pour in vegetable or chicken stock and bring to a simmer.\n    28→6. Simmer for 15 minutes until cucumbers are tender.\n    29→7. Add fresh dill and lemon juice.\n    30→8. Season with salt and white pepper to taste.\n    31→9. For creamy version, stir in sour cream just before serving.\n    32→10. Serve hot in winter or chill thoroughly and serve cold.\n    33→\n    34→SERVING SUGGESTIONS:\n    35→Top with dollop of sour cream and fresh dill sprig. Serve with dark rye bread.\n    36→Can be made 1 day ahead and stored in refrigerator.\n    37→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkGVRfuYHRcmb4gr5mY2s8","session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"8d45e47c-2ac8-4ef6-bf24-0ea49bd100a2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BaLJzMTN6CcM8TvXXwnptH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→VEGETABLES\n     2→\n     3→Roasted Asparagus with Parmesan\n     4→\n     5→Simple yet elegant vegetable dish that complements\n     6→any main course. Perfect for spring and early summer.\n     7→\n     8→Ingredients:\n     9→- 2 lbs (900g) fresh asparagus,\n    10→  trimmed\n    11→- 3 tablespoons olive oil\n    12→- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n    13→- 1/2 cup grated parmesan cheese\n    14→- 1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n    15→- Zest of 1 lemon\n    16→- Salt and pepper to taste\n    17→- Fresh basil leaves\n    18→\n    19→Instructions:\n    20→Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).\n    21→Toss asparagus with olive oil, garlic, salt, pepper.\n    22→Spread on baking sheet in single layer.\n    23→Roast 12-15 minutes until tender-crisp. 45\n    24→Sprinkle with parmesan, lemon zest, pepper flakes.\n    25→Return to oven for 2 minutes.\n    26→Garnish with fresh basil.\n    27→Serves 4-6.\n    28→Best served immediately while warm."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SkGVRfuYHRcmb4gr5mY2s8","session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"242c8527-a0f1-4c89-9038-47b959a13fa9"}
