{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0129rvF9mRDG3QqAx4frz6kb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have the complete file. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of each function you requested:\n\n## Title Extractor Deep Dive\n\n### 1. **`passesHardFilters` function - All 9 Hard Filters**\n\n```typescript\nfunction passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean {\n  if (text.length < 3 || text.length > 80) return false;\n  if (looksLikeIngredient(text)) return false;\n  if (startsWithNumber(text)) return false;\n  if (looksLikeMetadata(text)) return false;\n  if (isLikelyGarbled(text)) return false;\n  if (looksLikeCookingInstruction(text)) return false;\n  if (text.includes(\" | \")) return false;  // Pipe-separated book category headers\n  if (/\\s{3,}\\d{1,4}\\s*$/.test(text)) return false;  // Trailing page numbers\n  if ((text.match(/\\//g) || []).length >= 2) return false;  // 2+ slash navigation breadcrumbs\n  // Plus 8 additional checks below...\n  if (/^\\s*[-•*]\\s/.test(text)) return false;  // Bullet-list items\n  if (/^For the\\s+/i.test(text) && /:\\s*$/.test(text)) return false;  // Sub-section headers\n  if (/:\\s*$/.test(text.trim()) && !/ : /.test(text)) return false;  // Lines ending with \":\"\n  if (/^Page\\s+\\d+/i.test(text.trim())) return false;  // \"Page 234\" navigation\n  if (/^Strona\\s+\\d+/i.test(text.trim())) return false;  // Polish \"Strona 234\"\n  if (/^\\[CORRUPTED\\s+SPILLOVER/i.test(text.trim())) return false;  // OCR spillover markers\n  if (/^\\(OCR\\b/i.test(text.trim())) return false;  // \"(OCR ...\" annotation lines\n  if (/^\\(.*\\bcorruption\\b/i.test(text.trim())) return false;  // Corruption notes\n  if (/^\\[.*\\]$/.test(text.trim())) return false;  // \"[CATEGORY TAGS]\"\n  if (isSectionLabel(text)) return false;  // Section labels (INGREDIENTS, etc.)\n  if (words.length === 1 && NON_TITLE_WORDS.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) return false;  // Single non-title words\n  if (words.length >= 8 && !/ [+:&/] /.test(text)) return false;  // 8+ words without separators\n  return true;\n}\n```\n\n**Summary**: 18+ cumulative filters (hard filters + sub-checks):\n1. Length: 3-80 characters\n2. Not an ingredient\n3. Not starting with number/fraction\n4. Not metadata (serves, prep time, etc.)\n5. Not garbled OCR\n6. Not a cooking instruction\n7. Not pipe-separated navigation\n8. No trailing page numbers (3+ spaces + digits)\n9. Not 2+ slash breadcrumbs (>= 2 slashes)\n10-18. Plus 9 additional sub-checks for bullets, sub-sections, page refs, corruption markers, section labels, single non-title words, and 8+ word non-compound lines\n\n---\n\n### 2. **`findBurstEnd` function - Spillover Detection**\n\n```typescript\nfunction findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number {\n  let i = 0;\n\n  // Skip overflow preambles: \"PREVIOUS RECIPE OVERFLOW\", \"SPILLOVER\", \"CONTINUATION\", \"CORRUPTED SECTION\"\n  const OVERFLOW_MARKERS = /\\b(PREVIOUS\\s+(RECIPE|PAGE)\\s+(OVERFLOW|CONTENT)|SPILLOVER|CONTINUATION|CORRUPTED\\s+SECTION)\\b/i;\n  let overflowEnd = 0;\n  for (let k = 0; k < lines.length && k < 30; k++) {\n    if (overflowEnd > 0 && k < overflowEnd) continue;\n    if (OVERFLOW_MARKERS.test(lines[k].text)) {\n      let m = k + 1;\n      let consecutiveBlanks = 0;\n      while (m < lines.length) {\n        const lineText = lines[m].text;\n        // Stop at visual separator (4+ dashes/equals)\n        if (/^[=\\-]{4,}$/.test(lineText)) {\n          overflowEnd = m + 1;\n          break;\n        }\n        // Track consecutive blank lines (2 = section boundary)\n        if (lineText.trim().length === 0) {\n          consecutiveBlanks++;\n          if (consecutiveBlanks >= 2) {\n            overflowEnd = m + 1;\n            break;\n          }\n        } else {\n          consecutiveBlanks = 0;\n          // Stop at ALL_CAPS line with 2+ words (next recipe heading)\n          if (isAllCaps(lineText) && wordCount(lineText) >= 2) {\n            overflowEnd = m;\n            break;\n          }\n        }\n        m++;\n      }\n      if (overflowEnd === 0) overflowEnd = m;\n    }\n  }\n  if (overflowEnd > 0) i = overflowEnd;\n\n  // Skip short garbled lines (< 20 chars, isLikelyGarbled, not ALL_CAPS)\n  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text) && !isAllCaps(lines[i].text)) {\n    i++;\n  }\n\n  // Skip long instruction prologues: 3+ consecutive cooking instructions\n  if (i === 0) {\n    let j = 0;\n    while (j < lines.length && looksLikeCookingInstruction(lines[j].text)) j++;\n    if (j >= 3) i = j;\n  }\n\n  // Skip prose prologues: 3+ consecutive body-text lines (lowercase start or sentence-ending with 4+ words)\n  if (i === 0) {\n    let j = 0;\n    while (j < lines.length) {\n      const t = lines[j].text;\n      const isBodyText = (\n        /^[a-ząćęłńóśźż]/.test(t) ||\n        t.endsWith(\",\") ||\n        (t.endsWith(\".\") && wordCount(t) > 4)\n      ) && wordCount(t) >= 4;\n      if (isBodyText) j++;\n      else break;\n    }\n    if (j >= 3) i = j;\n  }\n  return i;\n}\n```\n\n**How spillover detection works**:\n- Scans first 30 lines for overflow markers (PREVIOUS RECIPE OVERFLOW, SPILLOVER, CONTINUATION, CORRUPTED SECTION)\n- When found, jumps forward to the next section boundary (4+ dash/equals line, 2 consecutive blank lines, or ALL_CAPS heading with 2+ words)\n- Then skips short garbled lines (< 20 chars)\n- Skips long instruction prologues (3+ consecutive cooking instructions)\n- Skips prose prologues (3+ body-text lines with lowercase starts or comma/period continuations)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **`isTitleAbsentPage` function**\n\n```typescript\nfunction isTitleAbsentPage(lines: Array<string>): boolean {\n  const nonEmptyLines = lines.map(l => l.trim()).filter(l => l.length > 0);\n\n  if (nonEmptyLines.length < 3) return false;\n\n  const first3 = nonEmptyLines.slice(0, 3);\n\n  return first3.every(line =>\n    looksLikeIngredient(line) ||\n    looksLikeCookingInstruction(line) ||\n    isBodyProse(line)\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Detects pages where OCR captures start mid-recipe with no title. Returns `true` if all of the first 3 non-empty lines are ingredients, cooking instructions, or body prose.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **`isSectionLabel` and `looksLikeMetadata` functions**\n\n```typescript\nfunction isSectionLabel(text: string): boolean {\n  const normalized = stripDiacritics(text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase());\n  if (SECTION_LABELS.has(normalized)) return true;\n  // OCR variant: leading \"l\" may be OCR-corrupted \"I\"\n  const ocrNormalized = normalized.replace(/^l/, \"i\");\n  if (ocrNormalized !== normalized && SECTION_LABELS.has(ocrNormalized)) return true;\n  return false;\n}\n\nfunction looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n}\n```\n\n**`isSectionLabel`**: Matches against a predefined set of recipe section headers (INGREDIENTS, DIRECTIONS, PREPARATION, etc. in English and Polish). Strips diacritics for OCR resilience. Also handles OCR variant where \"l\" is misrecognized as \"I\" (lngredients → ingredients).\n\n**`looksLikeMetadata`**: Tests against METADATA_PATTERNS regex set including:\n- SERVES/MAKES/YIELDS patterns\n- PREP/COOK/PROOF/RISING TIME patterns\n- Polish patterns: NA OKOŁO, DLA + OSÓB, DLA + digit\n- Time units: \\d+ MIN, \\d+ GODZ\n- Season/category: SEZON, KATEGORIA, RODZAJ, PORCJI, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **`OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN` regex**\n\n```typescript\nconst OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN = /[0-9¡Íí€]/;\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Identifies lines containing commonly OCR-corrupted characters:\n- `0` → should be `o`\n- `1` → should be `i` or `l`\n- `4` → should be `a`\n- `5` → should be `s`\n- `¡` → should be `i`\n- `Í`, `í` → should be `i` or `l`\n- `€` → should be `e`\n\nUsed to flag candidates for blind OCR repair.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **`buildCandidates` function flow with blind OCR repair**\n\n```typescript\nfunction buildCandidates(lines: Array<string>): \n  { candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }>; burstEnd: number } {\n  \n  // Step 1: Extract non-empty lines\n  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Step 2: Find burst end (spillover detection)\n  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n\n  // Step 3: Pre-join hyphen-broken lines (\"CHICKEN WITH ROOT VEGET-\" + \"ABLES\")\n  for (let hi = burstEnd; hi < nonEmptyLines.length - 1; hi++) {\n    if (nonEmptyLines[hi].text.endsWith(\"-\")) {\n      const joined = nonEmptyLines[hi].text.slice(0, -1) + nonEmptyLines[hi + 1].text;\n      nonEmptyLines[hi] = { text: joined, index: nonEmptyLines[hi].index };\n      nonEmptyLines.splice(hi + 1, 1);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Step 4: Pre-merge consecutive short ALL_CAPS lines (OCR-fragmented headings)\n  // \"ROASTED CHICKEN\" + \"WITH ROOT\" → \"ROASTED CHICKEN WITH ROOT\"\n  const capsCoalesced = [...];\n  // ... merging logic ...\n\n  // Step 5: Pre-merge continuation lines (lines starting with /&+:( )\n  const mergedLines = [...];\n  // ... merging logic ...\n\n  // Step 6: Generate single-line candidates with hard-filter pass\n  for (let i = 0; i < mergedLines.length; i++) {\n    const line = mergedLines[i];\n    \n    // Strip page numbers and parenthetical glosses\n    const singleText = repairOcrText(stripParentheticalGloss(stripPageNumber(line.text)));\n    \n    if (passesHardFilters(singleText)) {\n      candidates.push({ text: singleText, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n    }\n\n    // BLIND OCR REPAIR: For early-position candidates (line.index <= 5) with OCR artifacts,\n    // generate an additional candidate with speculative digit→letter repair.\n    // This gives the embedding scorer a clean version even when dictionary repair misses.\n    if (line.index <= 5 && OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN.test(line.text)) {\n      const blindRepaired = applyBlindOcrRepair(singleText);\n      if (blindRepaired !== singleText && passesHardFilters(blindRepaired)) {\n        candidates.push({ text: blindRepaired, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Step 7: Generate 2-line joins (skip if first line is section label with <= 2 words)\n    if (i + 1 < mergedLines.length) {\n      const joined2 = repairOcrText(`${line.text} ${mergedLines[i + 1].text}`);\n      const shouldBlock2 = isSectionLabel(line.text) && \n        (wordCount(joined2) <= 2 || isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel(line.text));\n      if (!shouldBlock2 && passesHardFilters(joined2)) {\n        candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Step 8: Generate 3-line joins (same blocking logic)\n    if (i + 2 < mergedLines.length) {\n      const joined3 = repairOcrText(`${line.text} ${mergedLines[i + 1].text} ${mergedLines[i + 2].text}`);\n      const shouldBlock3 = isSectionLabel(line.text) && \n        (wordCount(joined3) <= 2 || isAlwaysBlockJoinLabel(line.text));\n      if (!shouldBlock3 && passesHardFilters(joined3)) {\n        candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Step 9: Cap at 25 candidates (prioritize ALL_CAPS and short ones)\n  if (candidates.length > 25) {\n    const prioritized = candidates.slice().sort((a, b) => {\n      const aAllCaps = isAllCaps(a.text) ? 0 : 1;\n      const bAllCaps = isAllCaps(b.text) ? 0 : 1;\n      if (aAllCaps !== bAllCaps) return aAllCaps - bAllCaps;\n      const aShort = wordCount(a.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n      const bShort = wordCount(b.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n      return aShort - bShort;\n    });\n    return { candidates: prioritized.slice(0, 25), burstEnd: ... };\n  }\n\n  return { candidates, burstEnd: ... };\n}\n```\n\n**Flow summary**:\n1. Extract non-empty lines\n2. Use `findBurstEnd` to skip spillover preambles\n3. Pre-join hyphen-broken lines\n4. Coalesce consecutive short ALL_CAPS fragments\n5. Pre-merge continuation lines (starting with `/&+:(`)\n6. Generate single-line candidates, passing hard filters\n7. **BLIND OCR REPAIR**: For lines at position ≤5 with OCR artifacts, speculatively apply digit→letter repair to generate additional clean candidates\n8. Generate 2-line joins (with section-label blocking logic)\n9. Generate 3-line joins (same blocking)\n10. Cap at 25 candidates (ALL_CAPS and short ones prioritized)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Scoring and bonus application in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings`**\n\n```typescript\n// Pass 1: Compute rawScore for all candidates\nconst rawScored = [];\nfor (const candidate of candidates) {\n  const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n  const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n  const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n  const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n  const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);  // Distance from headers/noise\n  rawScored.push({ ..., rawScore, embedding });\n}\n\n// Pass 2: Apply bonuses\nconst scored = rawScored.map((rs, candidateIndex) => {\n  // Position factor: candidate-relative position (amplifies existing signal)\n  const candidateRelativePosition = candidateIndex / rawScored.length;\n  const positionFactor = candidateRelativePosition < 0.5\n    ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - candidateRelativePosition * 2)\n    : 1.0;\n\n  // ALL_CAPS bonus: +0.08 for multi-word, +0.03 for single-word\n  const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n    ? (wordCount(rs.text) >= 2 ? 0.08 : 0.03)\n    : 0;\n\n  // Structural heading bonus: +0.10 for best ALL_CAPS heading\n  const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n\n  // thresholdScore: excludes structural bonus (prevents inflation on multi-recipe pages)\n  const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n  // baseScore: excludes position factor\n  const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n  // Final score: includes position factor\n  const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n\n  return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n});\n\n// Additional bonuses (applied after initial scoring):\n\n// First-after-preamble bonus: +0.08 to +0.12 when all preceding lines were filtered/empty/section labels\nif (firstCandidate.position > 0) {\n  const allPrecedingFiltered = lines.slice(0, firstCandidate.position).every(line => {\n    const trimmed = line.trim();\n    return trimmed === \"\" || !passesHardFilters(trimmed) || isSectionLabel(trimmed);\n  });\n  if (allPrecedingFiltered) {\n    const hasStructuralPreamble = lines.slice(0, firstCandidate.position).some(line => {\n      const trimmed = line.trim();\n      return trimmed !== \"\" && (isSectionLabel(trimmed) || looksLikeMetadata(trimmed) || trimmed.includes(\" | \"));\n    });\n    const preambleBonus = hasStructuralPreamble ? 0.12 : 0.08;\n    firstCandidate.score += preambleBonus;\n  }\n}\n\n// Direct-successor bonus: +0.10 when previous line is section label/metadata/pipe-separated (for top 3 only)\nfor (let ci = 0; ci < scored.length && ci <= 2; ci++) {\n  const candidate = scored[ci];\n  if (candidate.position > 0) {\n    const prevLine = lines[candidate.position - 1]?.trim() ?? \"\";\n    const prevIsHeader = isSectionLabel(prevLine) || looksLikeMetadata(prevLine) || prevLine.includes(\" | \");\n    if (prevIsHeader) {\n      candidate.score += 0.10;\n      candidate.baseScore += 0.10;\n      candidate.thresholdScore += 0.10;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// Cap combined positional boost to +0.15 max\n// (avoids over-boosting when multiple bonuses fire together)\n\n// Bilingual title detection: suppress translation candidates before thresholding\n// (prevents ALL_CAPS bonus from inflating threshold)\n\n// Subtitle suppression: -0.15 penalty for longer candidates following short position-0 title\n\n// Bilingual layout boost: +0.15 for position-0 candidate when followed by mixed-case\n// translation and then section label\n\n// Threshold calculation (uses thresholdScore to exclude structural bonus)\nconst bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map(s => s.thresholdScore));\nconst threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n\n// Filter candidates that pass threshold\nlet selected = scoredForThreshold.filter(s => s.score >= threshold);\n```\n\n**Bonus summary**:\n1. **rawScore**: `titleSimilarity - max(headerSimilarity, noiseSimilarity)`\n2. **positionFactor**: 1.0-1.12× multiplier (early candidates get boost)\n3. **allCapsBonus**: +0.08 (multi-word) or +0.03 (single-word)\n4. **structuralBonus**: +0.10 (best ALL_CAPS heading)\n5. **preambleBonus**: +0.08 to +0.12 (first after filtered/section preamble)\n6. **successorBonus**: +0.10 (follows section label/metadata)\n7. **Cap on positional boost**: max +0.15 combined\n8. **bilingual suppression**: translation candidates removed before thresholding\n9. **subtitlePenalty**: -0.15 for longer candidates after short position-0\n10. **bilingualLayoutBoost**: +0.15 for position-0 in bilingual layout\n\n**Threshold**: `max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7)`\n\n---\n\n### 8. **`looksLikeCookingInstruction` function**\n\n```typescript\nfunction looksLikeCookingInstruction(text: string): boolean {\n  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  if (words.length < 4) return false;  // Instructions are multi-word sentences\n\n  if (COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS.test(text.trim())) return true;\n  if (POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS.test(text.trim())) return true;\n  return false;\n}\n\n// English cooking verbs\nconst COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS = /^(beat|fold|stir|mix|add|pour|bake|cook|cool|remove|place|combine|whisk|knead|roll|spread|brush|slice|chop|dice|mince|drain|rinse|peel|grate|melt|simmer|boil|fry|sauté|saute|roast|grill|broil|steam|let|set|transfer|serve|garnish|arrange|sprinkle|season|preheat|cover|uncover|reduce|bring|toss|cut|trim|shape|form|scatter|score|pat|rub|skim|strain|heat|discard|rest|marinate|wrap|flip|turn|layer|stuff|drizzle|squeeze|zest|soak|thaw|freeze|chill|warm|toast|crush|pound|crack|break|separate|weigh|measure|sift|dust|coat|dip|dredge|baste|debone|butterfly|truss|shred|puree|blend|process|pulse|whip|cream|proof|rise|punch|divide|portion|assemble)\\b/i;\n\n// Polish cooking verbs (OCR-resilient forms without diacritics)\nconst POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS = /^(podawaj|dodaj|dodawaj|sma[zż]|gotuj|odced[zź]|wymieszaj|mieszaj|wlej|nalej|przygotuj|zagotuj|pokr[oó]j|obierz|wrzuc|wrzuć|usma[zż]|podsma[zż]|prze[lł][oó][zż]|zblenduj|ubij|roztrzepaj|rozprowad[zź]|wyrob|zamieszaj|posyp|polej|odstaw|na[lł][oó][zż]|przykryj|odkryj|wstaw|zdejmij|ods[aą]cz|rozgrzej|posiekaj|zetrzyj|wy[lł][oó][zż]|wyjmij|ukr[oó]j|przekr[oó]j|formuj|ugniataj|rozwałkuj)\\b/i;\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Identifies lines that are cooking instructions (not titles). Must be:\n1. Multi-word (4+ words minimum)\n2. Start with a cooking imperative verb (English or Polish)\n\nExamples: \"Beat eggs until fluffy\", \"Add flour to the mixture\", \"Dodaj mąkę do mieszaniny\"\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive analysis covers all 8 key functions and their roles in the title extraction pipeline. The system uses a multi-stage approach: hard filters → candidate generation → spillover detection → embedding scoring → threshold filtering → deduplication → normalization."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adc9a99c950d110e7 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 110888\ntool_uses: 5\nduration_ms: 86384</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"05f9d1f3-99b1