{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VTKjZvKHYstS4Mp2sWWmW9","type":"tool_result","content":"FISH & SEAFOOD\n\nHalibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\n\nAn elegant fish dish with a subtle floral note from\nsaffron. Perfect for entertaining.\n\nIngredients:\n- 4 halibut fillets (150g each)\n- 1 teaspoon saffron threads\n- 1/4 cup hot water\n- 200ml heavy cream\n- 2 shallots, finely diced\n- 100ml dry white wine\n- 2 tablespoons butter\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and white pepper\n- Fresh dill for garnish\n- 1 lemon, for serving\n\nInstructions:\nSteep saffron threads in hot water for 10 minutes. 67\nHeat butter and olive oil in pan over medium-high heat.\nSeason halibut with salt and pepper.\nCook fillets 4-5 minutes per side until cooked through.\nRemove and keep warm.\nIn same pan, sauté shallots until softened.\nAdd white wine, reduce by half.\nPour in saffron water and cream.\nSimmer 3-4 minutes until slightly thickened.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"f93e2b0d-02d8-4a7d-b617-f3b0a2b27362","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"FISH & SEAFOOD\n\nHalibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\n\nAn elegant fish dish with a subtle floral note from\nsaffron. Perfect for entertaining.\n\nIngredients:\n- 4 halibut fillets (150g each)\n- 1 teaspoon saffron threads\n- 1/4 cup hot water\n- 200ml heavy cream\n- 2 shallots, finely diced\n- 100ml dry white wine\n- 2 tablespoons butter\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- Salt and white pepper\n- Fresh dill for garnish\n- 1 lemon, for serving\n\nInstructions:\nSteep saffron threads in hot water for 10 minutes. 67\nHeat butter and olive oil in pan over medium-high heat.\nSeason halibut with salt and pepper.\nCook fillets 4-5 minutes per side until cooked through.\nRemove and keep warm.\nIn same pan, sauté shallots until softened.\nAdd white wine, reduce by half.\nPour in saffron water and cream.\nSimmer 3-4 minutes until slightly thickened.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
