{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WqojtPVGmWcK1oVRuheAhL","type":"tool_result","content":"Reduce heat and stir in the remaining stock, one ladle at a time, until the rice is\ncreamy but still al dente, about 18-20 minutes. The risotto should flow slightly on the plate.\nSeason with salt and white pepper. Finish with butter and grated Parmigiano-Reggiano.\n\nCARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\n\nSlice the swordfish paper-thin. Arrange on chilled plates. Dress with extra virgin olive oil,\nlemon juice, and sea salt. Scatter thinly shaved fennel and microgreens. Serve immediately.\n\nPreparation: 10 minutes\nServes: 4\n\nCARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\n\nPlace thin slices on a cold plate. Whisk together lemon, lime, orange juice with good quality\noil. Season with fıne sea salt and crushed coriander seeds. Garnish with fresh herbs and\nthinly sliced radish.\n\nnto a loured work counter and knead until smooth, approx 8 minutes. Proof in oiled bowl, cover\nwith damp cloth, 45 minutes at room temperature. Shape into ½ dozen rounds. Second proof 30 min.\n\nPlace pans in 225°C/435-VI0.. oven for 12-15 minutes until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.\n\nMakes: 1 dozen\n\nFRESH PASTA DOUGH\n\n125 grams plain flour\n½ cup plus ı tablespoon water\nPinch of sea salt\n\nCombine flour and slt on work bench. Make well in center. Add water gradually, mixing with fork\nuntil dough comes together. Knead 5 minutes.\n\nMushroom Risotto\n\nIngredients:\n300g arborio rice\n1 liter vegetable stock\n250g mixed mushrooms, sliced","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"51512dd8-8ef6-4f0a-abe0-3d259be0ac48","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"Reduce heat and stir in the remaining stock, one ladle at a time, until the rice is\ncreamy but still al dente, about 18-20 minutes. The risotto should flow slightly on the plate.\nSeason with salt and white pepper. Finish with butter and grated Parmigiano-Reggiano.\n\nCARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\n\nSlice the swordfish paper-thin. Arrange on chilled plates. Dress with extra virgin olive oil,\nlemon juice, and sea salt. Scatter thinly shaved fennel and microgreens. Serve immediately.\n\nPreparation: 10 minutes\nServes: 4\n\nCARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\n\nPlace thin slices on a cold plate. Whisk together lemon, lime, orange juice with good quality\noil. Season with fıne sea salt and crushed coriander seeds. Garnish with fresh herbs and\nthinly sliced radish.\n\nnto a loured work counter and knead until smooth, approx 8 minutes. Proof in oiled bowl, cover\nwith damp cloth, 45 minutes at room temperature. Shape into ½ dozen rounds. Second proof 30 min.\n\nPlace pans in 225°C/435-VI0.. oven for 12-15 minutes until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.\n\nMakes: 1 dozen\n\nFRESH PASTA DOUGH\n\n125 grams plain flour\n½ cup plus ı tablespoon water\nPinch of sea salt\n\nCombine flour and slt on work bench. Make well in center. Add water gradually, mixing with fork\nuntil dough comes together. Knead 5 minutes.\n\nMushroom Risotto\n\nIngredients:\n300g arborio rice\n1 liter vegetable stock\n250g mixed mushrooms, sliced","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
