{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X18gEndaH1EZcy81weHdyj","type":"tool_result","content":"Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | PRZYGOTOWANIE 15 MIN | GOTOWANIE 20 MIN\n\nOGÓRKOWA ZUPA\n\nOgórkowa zupa, or Polish cucumber soup, is a refreshing summer soup served\neither hot or cold. The dill-infused broth is bright and tangy, perfect for\nwarm days when you want something light yet satisfying and nourishing.\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n- 6 medium cucumbers, peeled and diced\n- 6 cups vegetable or chicken stock\n- 1 large onion, diced\n- 2 tbsp butter\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 3 tbsp fresh dill, chopped\n- 2 tbsp fresh lemon juice\n- 1/2 cup sour cream\n- 1/4 tsp white pepper\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh dill sprigs for garnish\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. In a large pot, melt butter over medium heat.\n2. Sauté diced onion until translucent, about 5 minutes.\n3. Add minced garlic and cook 1 minute more.\n4. Add diced cucumbers and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n5. Pour in vegetable or chicken stock and bring to a simmer.\n6. Simmer for 15 minutes until cucumbers are tender.\n7. Add fresh dill and lemon juice.\n8. Season with salt and white pepper to taste.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"da6037f1-0c01-4817-94f5-63daaf88afa1","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | PRZYGOTOWANIE 15 MIN | GOTOWANIE 20 MIN\n\nOGÓRKOWA ZUPA\n\nOgórkowa zupa, or Polish cucumber soup, is a refreshing summer soup served\neither hot or cold. The dill-infused broth is bright and tangy, perfect for\nwarm days when you want something light yet satisfying and nourishing.\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n- 6 medium cucumbers, peeled and diced\n- 6 cups vegetable or chicken stock\n- 1 large onion, diced\n- 2 tbsp butter\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 3 tbsp fresh dill, chopped\n- 2 tbsp fresh lemon juice\n- 1/2 cup sour cream\n- 1/4 tsp white pepper\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh dill sprigs for garnish\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. In a large pot, melt butter over medium heat.\n2. Sauté diced onion until translucent, about 5 minutes.\n3. Add minced garlic and cook 1 minute more.\n4. Add diced cucumbers and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n5. Pour in vegetable or chicken stock and bring to a simmer.\n6. Simmer for 15 minutes until cucumbers are tender.\n7. Add fresh dill and lemon juice.\n8. Season with salt and white pepper to taste.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
