{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VCdFiFeLZoBgY9oBzT7Yvc","type":"tool_result","content":"[CORRUPTED TEXT FROM PREVIOUS PAGE - PARTIAL RECIPE]\nIngredients (continued):\n- 3 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 teaspoon cinnamon\n- ½ cup brown sugar\n- ¾ cup walnuts, coarsely chopped\n- 1/4 teaspoon sea salt\n- Zest of 2 limes\n\nınstructions for the Base Layer:\nCream together the softened butter (½ cup plus ı tablespoon) with\nthe granulated sugar at high speed for ı2-ı4 minutes. The mixture\nshould be pale and fluffy. Gently fold nto the dry ingredients.\n\nBake at 180°C/350-VI5 degrees for 28-32 minutes until the edges are\nset but the center still yields slightly to pressure.\n\nLet cool completely before serving with whipped cream and crushed\npistachio garnish. This dessert keeps in an aırtight contaıner for\nup to 4 days.\n\n---\n\nPEACH COBBLER\n\nIngredients for Filling:\n- 4 lbs fresh peaches, peeled and sliced\n- ½ cup granulated sugar\n- ¼ cup brown sugar\n- 2 tablespoons cornstarch\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- ½ teaspoon almond extract\n- ¼ teaspoon nutmeg\n- Pinch of salt\n- Juice of ½ lemon\n\nFor the Topping:\n- 2 cups all-purpose flour\n- ½ cup granulated sugar\n- 2 teaspoons baking powder\n- ¼ teaspoon salt\n- 6 tablespoons cold butter, cubed\n- ¾ cup buttermilk\n\nAssembly:\n1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C)\n2. Toss peaches with sugars, cornstarch, extracts, nutmeg, salt, lemon\n3. Spread filling in 9x13 baking dish\n4. Whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt\n5. Cut in cold butter until mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs\n6. Stir in buttermilk just until combined\n7. Drop spoonfuls of topping over peaches\n8. Bake 45-50 minutes until filling bubbles and topping is golden\n9. Cool 15 minutes before serving with vanilla ice cream","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"50c90a5a-35b4-4465-a4b8-651f793b9a48","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"