{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011smbLzgvrDkQ48T4ktUmkC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so `SECTION_LABELS` includes Polish food categories (warzywa, mieso, ryby, etc.) but NOT English ones. The English `CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS` has \"vegetables\", \"fish\", \"seafood\" etc. but `SECTION_LABELS` doesn't have \"vegetables\". Let me check more carefully:\n\nLooking at `SECTION_LABELS`:\n- English: ingredients, directions, instructions, method, preparation, steps, notes, etc. — NO food categories\n- Polish: includes both recipe sections (skladniki, przygotowanie) AND category labels (warzywa, mieso, ryby, zupy, etc.)\n\n\n- This creates an asymmetry where Polish food categories get filtered out but English ones like \"VEGETABLES\" and \"FISH & SEAFOOD\" pass through, which is clearly a bug.\n\nNow I'm identifying the root causes. The first major issue is the OCR blind repair logic that's replacing `1` with `l` instead of `i` in mixed-case mode, affecting several dish names like Braised Cod and Żurek Krakowski.\n\nSecond, English food categories like `VEGETABLES` and `FISH & SEAFOOD` aren't in the Polish-focused `SECTION_LABELS` list, so they pass the hard filters and can get boosted with the ALL_CAPS bonus.\n\nThird, the direct-successor bonus isn't accounting for blank lines between headers and titles—it's checking the immediately preceding line which is often empty.\n\nFourth, there's an issue with the overflow marker regex...\n\nThe overflow marker regex is too narrow—it expects `PREVIOUS PAGE OVERFLOW|CONTENT` or `CORRUPTED SECTION` but the actual text says `CORRUPTED TEXT FROM PREVIOUS PAGE`, which doesn't match.\n\nFifth, `findBurstEnd` can't handle mixed instruction and prose prologues that alternate between cooking steps and narrative text.\n\nFinally, mixed-case OCR corruption like `KoPyTka` doesn't trigger the ALL_CAPS repair path since it's not fully capitalized, so the character mapping doesn't fire correctly.\n\nNow I'm laying out the specific fixes needed and how to implement them.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1244,"cache_read_input_tokens":74157,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1244},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1b8cabe-82af-4d43-a6df-d4a8ec65d151","uuid":"73913c52-f1bb-4dcf-9361-0cd3f7a0b351"}
